Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane, has named his side’s La Liga El Clasico squad to face Barcelona at Camp Nou on Saturday. Zidane released a list of twenty players to tackle Barcelona in a post via the club’s official website on Friday. Real Madrid head to the game following a 3-2 defeat against Shakhtar Donetsk in the Champions League earlier this week, while Barcelona defeated Ferencvaros 5-1. Real Madrid’s squad against Barcelona: Goalkeepers: Courtois, Lunin and Luis López. Defenders: E. Militão, Sergio Ramos, R. Varane, Nacho, Marcelo and F. Mendy. Midfielders: Kroos, Modrić, Casemiro, Valverde and Isco. Forwards: Benzema, Asensio, Lucas V., Jović, Vini Jr., and Rodrygo. The kick-off time is scheduled at 3 pm, Nigerian time.